76561198138766144,Recommended,255260,14734417,"Posted: 4 March, 2015",all,Vasilis,"I really like the game, but it can be pretty buggy. A bug that particularly bothers me is the one where my riders get eliminated from a race after it has finished, and then telling me the next day they actually got injured. Once I even had a rider 'abandon' on a stage he actually won! That means no points, no palmares, no money and an unjust injury. This is particularly bothering after a hard-fought result, it only seems to happen to top-10 finishers. Also, quite a few don't register.However, I do like how the game works in general, although I hope that in future releases, Cyanide will focus on improving and debuggin the features they already have instead of adding new ones. The TTT, for one. Short ones are unwinnable and long ones are unlosable. Riders blocking their own teammates for another (I know they don't consider that a bug but a feature...), and incorrect comments as well (saying riders lose contact when they just got back for example.)I still recommend it, I think I have played more Pro Cycling Manager (2012&2014) than all other games combined... If you don't count Rome Total War.In my opinion this game is the closest to the real races any game ever got, with the advantage you have more impact on the results, so you can 'make sure' you bet on the right rider."
